{
  "texts": [
    "The gustatory system, which underpins taste perception, is primarily located on the tongue, where taste buds are situated.",
    "An adult typically has around 2,000 to 8,000 taste buds, with each containing approximately 50 to 100 receptor cells.",
    "These gustatory receptor cells respond to five primary taste modalities: sweetness, sourness, bitterness, saltiness, and umami.",
    "Each modality operates through distinct mechanisms.",
    "Sweet and umami tastes activate G-protein-coupled receptors, which trigger intracellular signaling cascades."
  ]
}